# Unit Tests Implementation Walkthrough

All the unit test cases from the [implementation_plan.md](file:///C:/Users/91961/.gemini/antigravity-ide/brain/9111ae7c-facb-47d8-af88-6877e233739e/implementation_plan.md) have been successfully written using the standard Go testing library and manual repository mock implementations.

## What was completed

The unit tests have been structured into the three main domains. Here is what has been tested:

### 1. Domain: Wallet
- **Model Tests**: [model_test.go](file:///c:/Users/91961/Documents/Yash_Work/Kulu/wallet-transfer-assignment/internal/domain/wallet/model_test.go)
  - Validation checks on wallet creation (e.g. enforcing presence of `ID`, `OwnerID`, `Currency`).
  - Active status checks via `IsActive()`.
- **Service Tests**: [service_test.go](file:///c:/Users/91961/Documents/Yash_Work/Kulu/wallet-transfer-assignment/internal/domain/wallet/service_test.go)
  - Full mocking of `wallet.Repository`.
  - Testing `Create` service and checking that it wraps repository errors properly.
  - Testing `GetByID` success and error paths.

### 2. Domain: Transfer
- **Model Tests**: [model_test.go](file:///c:/Users/91961/Documents/Yash_Work/Kulu/wallet-transfer-assignment/internal/domain/transfer/model_test.go)
  - Structural validation constraints (must have positive amount, unique sender and recipient wallets).
  - State machine transitions (`CanTransitionTo`) to ensure a transfer can only move from `PENDING` to `PROCESSED` or `FAILED`.
- **Service Tests**: [service_test.go](file:///c:/Users/91961/Documents/Yash_Work/Kulu/wallet-transfer-assignment/internal/domain/transfer/service_test.go)
  - Idempotency logic: checks if executing an existing `TxnID` early-returns the original status.
  - Multi-mocking environment to mimic `wallet.Repository` validation and `ledger.Service` execution.
  - Step-by-step failure validation: confirming errors roll up and update the transfer state to `FAILED` correctly across the execution workflow.

### 3. Domain: Ledger
- **Service Tests**: [service_test.go](file:///c:/Users/91961/Documents/Yash_Work/Kulu/wallet-transfer-assignment/internal/domain/ledger/service_test.go)
  - Includes mocks for the ledger-specific repositories (`LedgerRepository` and `BalanceRepository`), as well as a mock transactional system (`tx.Starter` and `tx.Tx`).
  - Validation of transaction integrity: verifying that on any individual failure (balance insufficient, DB down, commit fails), a `Rollback()` is triggered.
  - Verification that when all queries succeed, exactly two ledger entries (one Debit, one Credit) are pushed.

## How to execute

You can run the tests yourself directly via the terminal to observe the coverage and success cases:

```bash
go test -v -cover ./internal/domain/...
```

> [!TIP]
> The tests run exceptionally fast and safely as they use mock structs and do not actually hit the PostgreSQL driver.
